    content: "The Great Rann of Kutch in Gujarat is one of the largest salt deserts in the world. For half the year, the region is submerged under shallow seawater driven by the monsoon tides. As the water evaporates during the dry winter months, it leaves behind a vast crust of pure white salt that stretches to the horizon.\n\nDespite the high salinity and extreme temperatures, the Rann is home to unique wildlife, including the endangered Indian wild ass in the Little Rann, and serves as a major nesting ground for the Lesser Flamingo, showing how life can adapt to highly variable coastal environments.",
